data.name: comboBox_dbType.ToolTip
data.value: Database file type (format). This is important !! You must choose choose the correct format otherwsie comparing will not work.

data.name: checkBox_add_filters.Text
data.value: Add filters if available (i.e filters by region).

data.name: checkBox_add_filters.ToolTip
data.value: Some database formats include filter information (i.e. CSV includes rom region info for roms) If this option is set and the database supports filters, EO will import this information and add it as filters that can be used in the filters section.

data.name: checkBox_import_category.Text
data.value: Add categories into rom if available.

data.name: checkBox_import_category.ToolTip
data.value: Some database formats include category information (i.e. CSV includes rom category under Genre) If this option is set and the database tyüe supports category, EO will import this information into rom category as well.

data.name: button3.ToolTip
data.value: Reset the archive extesnions form parent console.

data.name: checkBox_turboe.ToolTip
data.value: Increase the process speed by removing the matched entry from the memory pool. This will increase process speed but reduce possiblities, for example, if the console contain the same file (inside an archive file or not) more that once, the first file detected as match get updated, the other same ones will not be matched.

data.name: checkBox_cahceOndisk.ToolTip
data.value:
If set, extract all archive content on disk before comparing. This may speed things up specially for nes console, whcih requires to calculate crc/md5.sha1 with header bytes skip.
The 7z has a bug when attempting to extract a single file. the whoile archive get extracted (and skipped) until the demanded file get extracted .... this will extremly slow the progress.
*WARNING: never ever set this option if the console contain archive files with huge sizes (above 50 MB)

data.name: checkBox_archive_perfect_match.Text
data.value: Perfect match (match all crcs of the archive file, MAME only)

data.name: checkBox_archive_perfect_match.ToolTip
data.value: Used by some databases (MAME for example) if set, all archive file content must match entries from the database until compared rom (the archive one) considered a match.

data.name: checkBox_forNesArchiveTweeks.Text
data.value: This database file is for nes (use speed methods for archive check)

data.name: checkBox_forNesArchiveTweeks.ToolTip
data.value: It's recommended to set this option if you are using a database for NES console. NES files with iNES extesnions require some tricky calculations due to header skip.

data.name: textBox_archive_extesnions.ToolTip
data.value: Only files with these extensions considerd COMPRESSED. The files with other extesnions will be treated as normal roms.

data.name: textBox_archivePassword.ToolTip
data.value: Password to use if the archive files are locked with a passwrod. Note that this password will be used for all compressed files.

data.name: label3.Text
data.value: If the archive file is locked, use this password:

data.name: checkBox_check_inside_archive.Text
data.value: If rom file is compressed, check inside it for match.

data.name: checkBox_check_inside_archive.ToolTip
data.value:
If set: If the rom file is compressd, the program will look inside of it (and extract its content if neccessary) for matched file.
Note that remaming (or database applying) will be made by the first entry that match any archive content file.

data.name: groupBox_parent_not_match.Text
data.value: When a parent rom DOES NOT MATCH any entry:

data.name: radioButton_parent_not_match_keep_parent_if_one_child_match.Text
data.value: Keep the parent only if at least one child match.

data.name: radioButton_parent_not_match_keep_parent_if_one_child_match.ToolTip
data.value:
Work only if "delete the roms not matched from console" is set.
If the rom is a parent rom, and that rom DOES NOT match any entry of the database, this option (if set) will keep the PARENT only if at least one child rom match an entry of the database. The matched child will stay with the parent as well, along with other matched children. For not matched children, you can set to remove them or not using the option below "delete children not match"

data.name: radioButton_parent_not_mathc_free_matched_children.Text
data.value: Remove the parent, keep the child that match and make it single (no parent nor child)

data.name: radioButton_parent_not_mathc_free_matched_children.ToolTip
data.value:
Work only if "delete the roms not matched from console" is set.
If the rom is a parent rom, and that rom DOES NOT match any entry of the database, this option (if set) will REMOVE the PARENT anyway. The matched child/children will stay and marked as SINGLE rom (not parent nor child)

data.name: checkBox_parent_not_match_keep_on_one_child_match_dont_keep_unmathced_children.ToolTip
data.value:
Work only if "delete the roms not matched from console" is set.
If the rom is a parent rom, and that rom DOES NOT match any entry of the database, this option (if set) will keep the PARENT only if at least one child rom match an entry of the database. The other children that not match will stay with the parent as well.

data.name: groupBox_parent_match.Text
data.value: When a parent rom matches an entry:

data.name: radioButton_parent_match_keep_all_children.Text
data.value: Keep its all children (matched or not)

data.name: radioButton_parent_match_keep_all_children.ToolTip
data.value:
Work only if "delete the roms not matched from console" is set.
If the rom is a parent rom, and that rom matches an entry from the database, this option (if set) will keep all the children roms (matched or not) of this parent along with the parent.

data.name: radioButton_parent_matche_keep_matched_only.Text
data.value: Keep the child that match (remove children that not match)

data.name: radioButton_parent_matche_keep_matched_only.ToolTip
data.value:
Work only if "delete the roms not matched from console" is set.
If the rom is a parent rom, and that rom matches an entry from the database, this option (if set) will keep only the child/children roms that match entry/entries of this parent along with the parent.
Not matched children will be removed from database (and from disk if the options aboce say so).

data.name: checkBox_delete_not_matched_related.Text
data.value: Delete the roms not matched related files as well (be careful !)

data.name: checkBox_delete_not_matched_related.ToolTip
data.value: If a rom not matched and need to be deleted (option above is set), delete the rom related file(s) from DISK as well. Related files can be images (snaps, covers ..etc), videos, sounds and everyfile assigned for this rom as information container tab. BE CAREFUL !!

data.name: checkBox_delete_not_matched_files.Text
data.value: Delete the roms not matched files as well (be careful !)

data.name: checkBox_delete_not_matched_files.ToolTip
data.value: If a rom not matched and need to be deleted (option above is set), delete the rom file from DISK as well. BE CAREFUL !!

data.name: checkBox_delete_roms_nott_found.Text
data.value: Delete the roms not matched from console.

data.name: checkBox_delete_roms_nott_found.ToolTip
data.value: Remove the rom that not matched from database.

data.name: radioButton_compare_rom_file_name.Text
data.value: Rom FILE name <-> Database entry file name

data.name: radioButton_compare_rom_file_name.ToolTip
data.value:
Compare : Rom FILE NAME with ENTRY NAMES.
WARNING: Very slow in some cases, specially with compressed roms. Please use this only if neccessary.

data.name: radioButton_compare_sha1.Text
data.value: Rom file SHA1 <-> Database entry SHA1

data.name: radioButton_compare_sha1.ToolTip
data.value:
Compare: Rom file SHA1 <-> ENTRY SHA1
For compressed file, you need to configure how's the sha1 should be compared.

data.name: radioButton_compare_md5.Text
data.value: Rom file MD5 <-> Database entry MD5

data.name: radioButton_compare_md5.ToolTip
data.value:
Compare: Rom file MD5 <-> ENTRY MD5
For compressed file, you need to configure how's the md5 should be compared.

data.name: radioButton_compare_crc.Text
data.value: Rom file CRC <-> Database entry CRC

data.name: radioButton_compare_crc.ToolTip
data.value:
Compare: Rom file CRC <-> ENTRY CRC
For compressed file, you need to configure how's the crc should be compared.

data.name: radioButton_compare_name.Text
data.value: Rom name <-> Database entry file name

data.name: radioButton_compare_name.ToolTip
data.value: Compare : Rom NAME with ENTRY NAMES.

data.name: checkBox_rename_parent.Text
data.value: If the rom is a parent rom, apply entry (rename, data info ...) on it.

data.name: checkBox_rename_parent.ToolTip
data.value:
If set: if a parent rom (compressed or not) matches an entry from the database, this parent get updated using that entry (naming, adding data elements ..etc)
Note that any matched child will be updated regadless of parent (this option is set or not) and will be treated as normal roms (using options above).

data.name: checkBox_apply_rom_data_info.Text
data.value: Apply rom data-info in rom from entry (if available)

data.name: checkBox_apply_rom_data_info.ToolTip
data.value: If set, matched roms (single and children roms) will take info data from database (if any) and add them as info data (displayed as column in roms list).

data.name: checkBox_rename_rom.Text
data.value: Rename rom (apply "Name" entry on it in "Name" rom property).

data.name: checkBox_rename_rom.ToolTip
data.value: If set, matched rom (single roms and children roms) will be renamed setting "Name" property of that rom.

data.name: label6.Text
data.value: For normal roms and children of parent roms:

data.name: label5.Text
data.value: WORK ONLY ON PARENT ROMS, CHILD ROMS WILL BE TREATED AS NORMAL ROMS (using options above):

data.name: richTextBox1.Text
data.value: * Please read options carrefully and configure this importer carrefully to get the needed results. * You can import the same database format file into the same console multible times and each time change the options to get the needed results. * After importing database format file, if there is a data-info that applyed into column and the content doesn't display correctly (usually named "Description", not enough room in column for that text), please note that you can use option "Data info to info Tab" from "Tools" main menu, this tool convert data-info data into text-info tab and save them in files. There is no other way around this issue.
